round-color: #ccc;"><em>terrified=C2=A0</em>of its users</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Reddit said its millions of loyal users and mo=
derators pose risks as well as a benefit for the company. Redditors have a =
historically combative relationship with the site, launching revolts over e=
verything from racism on the platform to executives=E2=80=99 staffing decis=
ions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Thousands of members of the WallStreetBets for=
um =E2=80=94 which boasts around 15 million users and helped popularize mem=
e stocks like GameStop Corp. =E2=80=94 voted to boost a forum post about sh=
orting Reddit=E2=80=99s stock when it begins trading. Their reasons varied =
from the company=E2=80=99s lack of profitability to competitive concerns.</=
p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One reason Reddit <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34768763.286358/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDItMjEvcmVkZGl0LXMtaXBvLWlzLWZvci1yZWRka=
XRvcnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMyMTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291=
cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwMzIxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5d1042bb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">sold=C2=A0some of its IPO stock</a=
>=C2=A0to its users was probably to buy their loyalty,=C2=A0to cause them t=
o be literally invested in Reddit=E2=80=99s success. You sell them stock, a=
nd they stick around to comment and moderate and provide value to advertise=
rs and artificial intelligence scrapers. You give them a nice IPO pop, and =
they are happy. They, you know, vote down the WallStreetBets post about sho=
rting the stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s a risky move! If you sell them =
stock at $34 and it=C2=A0<em>goes down</em>, they will be mad at you. They=
=E2=80=99ll vote up the post about shorting the stock; they=E2=80=99ll be s=
urly and mischievous on their subreddits. Maximizing the price at which you=
 sell the stock is nice, but not=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>important in the l=
ong run. Making sure that the Redditors who buy in the IPO have a good expe=
rience is probably more important.</p>
